# Badge

`TxBadge` renders a compact inline pill or dot indicator. It is intentionally not a target-wrapper badge; the default slot replaces the badge content instead of positioning the badge around another element.

Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/badge/src/types.ts`, `TxBadge.vue`, and `badge.test.ts`.

## Basic Usage

### Badge Variants

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BadgeBadgeVariantsDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <div class="tuff-demo-row">
      <TxBadge :value="8" />
      <TxBadge value="New" variant="primary" />
      <TxBadge value="99+" variant="success" />
      <TxBadge dot variant="error" />
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

## Composition Examples

### Custom Slot Content

```vue
<template>
  <TxBadge variant="primary">
    <strong>Beta</strong>
  </TxBadge>
</template>
```

### Custom Color

```vue
<template>
  <TxBadge value="Internal" color="#111827" />
</template>
```

### Dot Indicator

```vue
<template>
  <TxFlex align="center" gap="8px">
    <TxBadge dot variant="error" />
    <span>Service degraded</span>
  </TxFlex>
</template>
```

## Interaction Contract

- The root is an inline `span` with pill styling.
- `variant` controls default CSS variables for background, text, and border colors.
- `color` overrides the background via `--tx-badge-bg` and forces `--tx-badge-text: #ffffff`.
- When `dot=true`, the component renders `.tx-badge__dot`, adds `tx-badge--dot`, and does not render `value` or default slot text.
- When `dot=false`, the default slot takes priority over `value`.
- `value` defaults to `0`, so an empty badge still renders `0` unless a slot or `dot` is used.
- `TxBadge` has no click event, positioning logic, overflow truncation, or target anchoring behavior.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `variant` | `'default' \| 'primary' \| 'success' \| 'warning' \| 'error'` | `'default'` | Color preset. |
| `value` | `number \| string` | `0` | Badge text content when the default slot is not used and `dot=false`. |
| `color` | `string` | - | Custom background color. Also sets text color to white. |
| `dot` | `boolean` | `false` | Render a compact dot and hide text content. |

### Events

`TxBadge` does not emit component events. Attach interactions to surrounding controls when a badge needs to behave like a filter or notification target.

### Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `default` | - | Custom pill content. Ignored when `dot=true`. |

### CSS Variables

| Variable | Source | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `--tx-badge-bg` | `variant` / `color` | Badge background. |
| `--tx-badge-text` | `variant` / `color` | Badge text color. |
| `--tx-badge-border` | `variant` | Badge border color. |

## Best Practices

- Use `TxBadge` for counts and small state hints. Use `TxStatusBadge` when the label needs a status icon or permission mapping.
- Keep badge text short; `white-space: nowrap` prevents wrapping.
- For target-corner notification badges, position `TxBadge` in the host component. `TxBadge` does not anchor itself.
- Do not rely on dot color alone for critical states; pair dot indicators with adjacent text.
- Prefer variants for semantic states and reserve `color` for brand or custom taxonomy labels.

